Wash and dry all produce. Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2}, keeping greens and
whites separate. Mince @garlic{2%clove}. Core and seed @poblano pepper{1}, then cut into
½-inch squares. Drain and rinse @borlotti beans{1%box}.

> A mesh strainer is perfect for draining canned or boxed foods and more.

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%teaspoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add
@ground beef{10%ounce}, breaking it up into pieces. Cook, tossing occasionally,
until browned at the edges and no longer pink, ~{5-6%minutes}. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Remove from pan with a #slotted spoon{} and set aside.

Remove pan from heat and carefully pour out and discard any excess grease left by
beef. Return to medium-high heat and add scallion whites, poblano, and garlic.
Cook, tossing, until lightly browned and softened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add @Mexican spice blend{1%tablespoon} to pan and toss to coat veggies. Cook until
fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}. Season with salt and pepper.

Add @veggie stock concentrate{1}, beans, @crushed tomatoes{1%box}, beef, and
1 cup water to pan and stir to combine. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and let
simmer until thick and stew-like, about ~{10%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide chili between #bowls{}. Sprinkle with @cheddar cheese{1/2%cup} and scallion
greens. Dollop with @sour cream{4%tablespoon} and serve.